// Every license, permit/add-on, price, field, option, and officialNote/TODO
// below is preserved verbatim from that research file.
//
// Type-mapping decisions (JSON -> StateConfig union types):
//  - All 28 licenses use in-union residency (resident/nonresident/youth/senior)
//    and category (freshwater/saltwater/combo/other) values — NO remapping was
//    required. There is no "all-water" license: Florida sells freshwater and
//    saltwater separately; the Freshwater/Saltwater combo ($32.50) maps to
//    category "combo".
//  - All 30 formFields use in-union FieldTypes (text/select/radio/date/ssn/
//    email/tel/zip/checkbox) — no remapping required. No conditional rules
//    exist in the research (portal conditionals such as the mailing-address
//    block are documented as TODOs in the relevant fields' officialNote).
//  - The research top-level "sources" array is not part of StateConfig; it is
//    folded into researchNotes below so no provenance is dropped.
//  - The ssn field keeps the researched 9-raw-digit validation pattern from
//    the official form. NOTE (shared code, NOT modified): the shared
//    buildFieldSchema() applies its own dashed SSN_PATTERN (123-45-6789) to
//    ssn-typed fields and ignores field-level validation — reported to the
//    orchestrator.
// ============================================================================

